description:
The pr-reply command requires a PR ID or URL to be explicitly provided (prIdOrUrl is required in the interface).

**Location:** src/cli/commands/ado/pr-reply.ts

prIdOrUrl: {
  type: 'string',
  describe: 'PR ID or full PR URL',
  demandOption: true,  // <-- Required
}

In contrast, the other new commands (pr-comment, pr-update, comments) all support auto-detection from the current git branch using findPRByCurrentBranch().

**Suggestion:** For consistency, consider making prIdOrUrl optional in pr-reply and adding the same auto-detection logic:

if (!argv.prIdOrUrl) {
  const result = await findPRByCurrentBranch(project, repo);
  ...
}

This would allow users to simply run:
aide ado pr reply --thread 123 'My reply'

instead of requiring the PR ID every time.
